CanvasComments.BodyText: Pass a table with values to create new Application entries. Each row will create a new entry, with the given values in each field.

Set the FormId input to the ID of the DataPortal to map to by clicking the pencil icon and selecting it. This DataFlow uses the AppManagement DataPortal, called "Insurance Application" on the DataPortal creation page.
By using the InstanceId column returned by the first DataPortal Sync, we can update one of the initially created rows. The new row, without an InstanceId value, will create a new Application entry

Use the JoinColumns input to update existing entries, identifying them by their FirstName and LastName columns.
Use DeleteUnmatched to delete the new application not included in this input table.
Include ParentInstanceId in the table to add BeneficiarieInfo entries to multiple applications at once. Multiple entries can be added to each application
Delete Application instances, identifying those to delete by FirstName and LastName.

Running this DataFlow will delete all existing data in the AppManagement DataPortal!

Because some portions of the DataFlow depend on uniqueness of data, existing data is deleted at the outset. This allows you to run portions of the dataflow and see the effects on the DataPortal after each step.
